Package edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.queue

Class ArrayBasedQueue<E>

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.queue.AbstractQueue<E>
edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.queue.ArrayBasedQueue<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements stored in the queue
All Implemented Interfaces:
Queue<E>
public class ArrayBasedQueue<E> extends AbstractQueue<E>
The Array-based Queue is implemented as a circular array-based data structure to support efficient, O(1) worst-case Queue abstract data type behaviors. The internal array dynamically resizes using the doubling strategy to ensure O(1) amortized cost for adding to the queue.
Author:
Dr. King, Jeremiah Knizley
